bug.short_desc: bogus 'there are no portable drives found' when USB stick is inserted
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1239327 screenshot
Description of problem:
Whether inserted before or after mediawriter launch; whether partitioned and FAT formatted, or wipefs -a has been used, mediawriter does not recognize this Lexar USB stick for unknown reasons. No error messages.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): mediawriter-4.0.7-0.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Launch mediawriter 2. Choose an image to write 3. Insert 2GiB Lexar USB stick
Actual results:
Kernel sees the stick, but mediawriter denies seeing any devices.
Expected results:
The image is 1.5GiB, the stick is 2GiB, it should be possible to write to this stick.
Additional info:
mediawriter-4.0.8-0.fc25 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 25. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-f4b2752eaf
mediawriter-4.0.8-0.fc25 has been pushed to the Fedora 25 stable repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report.
